gomodel:SYNGO_2073  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: This paper shows that mIPSCs in nucleus reticularis thalami (nRT) neurons are mediated by alpha3-containing GABA-A-Rs. The paper uses a combination of channel properties finger printing (channel decay kinetics), protein expression/localization to synapses, and a pharmacological agent (zolpidem) that in the given concentration and gene expression distinguishes alpha1- from alpha3-containing GABA-A-Rs. Only alpha1-containing GABA-A-Rs have sensitivity to zolpidem at the used concentration.\n\nFig.4: Co-localization with gephyrin (marker protein of GABA/Glycine postsynaptic specialization) is shown.. Experimental description: \"Male Wistar rats (21-32 days old) were deeply anaesthetized...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2073" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

